uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.handlers.documents.parsers.codeml

Class CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.handlers.documents.parsers.codeml.CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser

  • public class CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to parse the convergentSites.out output from the modified codeml-ancestral package by Jason De Koning at evolutionarygenomics.com / U Colorado, and used in Castoe et al. (2009)'s paper on convergence in agamid lizards.

    Constructor should be called with a single File argument, this being the location of the convergentSites.out file. The constructor will then build a hash of node comparison IDs and site convergent/divergent probability data. This can then be polled by the getData() method.

    Note that general outputs (tree string, taxon list) can be pulled from the codeml-anc.out file using CodemlAncestralGeneralOutputParser

    Author:
    Joe Parker, Kitson Consulting / Queen Mary University of London
    See Also:
    evolutionarygenomics.com, codeml-ancestral README, uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.handlers.documents.parsers.codeml}, uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.handlers.documents.parsers.codeml.CodemlAncestralGeneralOutputParser}

      • getSitewiseBranchPairProbabilitiesIncludingSpecificNodeNumber

        public float[][] getSitewiseBranchPairProbabilitiesIncludingSpecificNodeNumber(int nodeNumber)
        Return all the sitewise (not-summed) divergent, convergent, parallel, strict-convergent probabilities for any branch-pair comparisons including a particular node number.

        This is presented as an [n][4] matrix.

        This method uses the BranchPairComparison#contains() method to search for nodes in the data.

        Parameters:
        nodeNumber - - an integer UID describing a node (tip or internal) in the data
        Returns:
        float[n][4] containing the divergent, convergent, parallel, strict-convergent probabilities for any branch-pair comparisons including the specified node number.

      • getSummedBranchPairProbabilitiesIncludingSpecificNodeNumber

        public float[] getSummedBranchPairProbabilitiesIncludingSpecificNodeNumber(int nodeNumber)
        Return all the sitewise (summed) divergent, convergent, parallel, strict-convergent probabilities for any branch-pair comparisons including a particular node number.

        This is achieved by taking column sums from an [n][4] matrix returned by the getSitewiseBranchPairProbabilitiesIncludingSpecificNodeNumber(int nodeNumber) method.

        That method uses the BranchPairComparison#contains() method to search for nodes.

        Parameters:
        nodeNumber - - an integer UID describing a node (tip or internal) in the data
        Returns:
        float[4] containing the summed divergent, convergent, parallel, strict-convergent probabilities for any branch-pair comparisons including the specified node number.
